title: Swimfin
summary: Swimfins, swim fins, diving fins, or flippers are finlike accessories worn on the feet, legs or hands[1]  and made from rubber, plastic, carbon fiber or combinations of these materials, to aid movement through the water in water sports activities such as swimming, bodyboarding, bodysurfing, float-tube fishing, kneeboarding, riverboarding, scuba diving, snorkeling, spearfishing, underwater hockey, underwater rugby and various other types of underwater diving.
